{% set sub_topics = knowledge | replace("，", ",") | split(",") if knowledge else [] %}
{% if sub_topics and count <= sub_topics|length %}
{% set assigned = sub_topics[:count]|map('trim')|list %}
user: Generate {{ count }} SFT training samples for the topic "{{ topic }}", each targeting a different sub-topic. Strictly follow this assignment:
{% for st in assigned %}
  Sample {{ loop.index }} -> sub-topic: {{ st }}
{%- endfor %}
Requirements: each sample must use a different difficulty (beginner/intermediate/advanced) and a different question type (qa, choice, judge, fill). No two samples should have similar question angles.
{% else %}
{% set sub_topic_list = sub_topics|map('trim')|join(', ') if sub_topics else '' %}
user: Generate {{ count }} diverse SFT training samples for the topic "{{ topic }}".
{% if sub_topics %}Every sub-topic below must be covered at least once — do not concentrate all samples on a few sub-topics: {{ sub_topic_list }}{% endif %}
The {{ count }} samples must cover a variety of difficulties (beginner, intermediate, advanced) and question types (qa, choice, judge, fill). No two samples should have similar question angles or structure.
{% endif %}
{% if knowledge %}Use the following background knowledge to ensure accuracy:
{{ knowledge }}{% endif %}
Output a pure JSON array only, no extra text:
[
  {
    "instruction": "user instruction",
    "output": "assistant answer"
  },
  ...
]
